The reason for this difference is due to the difference in layout structures.

 - In flexbox, `justify-content` applies directly to flex items.

 - In grid, `justify-content` applies to grid columns ([more details](https://stackoverflow.com/a/48571889/3597276)).

 - In flexbox, there is no `justify-items` property ([more details](https://stackoverflow.com/q/32551291/3597276))

 - In grid, `justify-items` applies to grid items ([more details](https://stackoverflow.com/a/48571889/3597276))

Hence, to make your layout work, use `justify-items` in grid and `justify-content` in flex.

